President  Nicolas Sarkozy  starts his
eG-8 summit on international technology, part of the French
presidency of the G-20. The two-day summit, chaired by Maurice
Lévy, Chairman & CEO, Publicis Groupe, will host executives from
all over the world.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
Court of Human Rights ruling on former Bawag Chief Executive
Helmut Elsner’s pre-trial imprisonment (11:00, Strasbourg)  Hermes family voting rights hearing at (14:00, Paris)  ECONOMY:
Production outlook indicator 8:45
Business confidence indicator 8:45  GOVERNMENT:
8:30 International Chamber of Commerce briefing on G20 CEO
Advisory Group
10:00 Sarkozy address start of e-G8 forum in Paris
11:30  Christine Lagarde appears on a panel with executives from
EBay, Vivendi, Google and Alcatel.
13:00 President Nicolas Sarkozy lunches with summit attendees
16:15 Foreign Minister Alain Juppe Meets Irish Deputy Prime
Minister Eamon Gilmore  EQUITIES:
*The CAC 40 Index fell 83.87, or 2.1 percent, to 3,906.98.
*The broader SBF 120 Index dropped 2 percent.  ANNUAL GENERAL MEETINGS
EDF SA 14:30
